 Price set for several reasons:

title: For Sale:  Minimalist IWB Kydex Holsters (Glock)
location: Seattle to Pullman, Washington, United States
postcontent:
Minimalist, genuine Kydex holster designed for IWB carry. Instead of using loops attached via screws (as is typical), the design uses a single integral loop. This means there are no screws to lose (for retention adjustment or otherwise) when it matters most. Fits Glock 34, 35, 31, 22, 17, 19, 23, 32, 33, 27, and 26. 

.080 thick OD Kydex used throughout. All edges have been rounded with 220 grit sandpaper for comfort. Minor design alterations are possible, send ideas along and I'll see if I can implement them. Future holsters will likely use .060 kydex for increased comfort.

If you're wondering how I can sell these for such a low price, here's why:
- The fold-over structure is much faster to manufacture than typical pancake styles. This greatly reduces my time-cost.
- No attached belt loop means I don't have to make the loop in the first place, and I don't have to buy attachment screws.
- I don't polish the edges. Polishing the edges of the holster (like on most expensive kydex holsters) takes a lot of time. I have found finishing the edges with 220 grit offers the same level of comfort and alignment, albeit without the "shiny" cool-factor. 
- Use of a single rivet instead of multiple rivets or a retention-adjustment screw lowers material cost and manufacturing complexity. Besides, screws can come loose which could cause the firearm to exit the holster.

These are made by myself in Washington State - help support a starving college student! 

Because I live/go to school in Pullman (Go Cougs), I understand that many Armslisters would have to drive a considerable distance to pick up their holster. Therefore, **I will ship for free to the lower 48**. If you live in AK or HI I'll give you a $5 credit towards shipping costs.
